1, 0.12105482071638107, -0.060631364583969116, -0.08480936288833618, 0.10562369972467422], "turn_range": [0, 2]}, {"id": "794edf3e-6032-4a6e-952f-ff60aa27efcf", "chunk_index": 1, "text": "USER: Creator Chose Not To Use Archive WarningsHarry Potter/Hermione GrangerHermione GrangerHarry PotterAlbus DumbledoreMinerva McGonagallRubeus HagridFilius FlitwickMadam PomfreyDobbyFirst TimeHurt/ComfortEmotional Hurt/ComfortSlow BurnPiningCanon DivergenceRoom of RequirementVaginal SexFluff and AngstHappy EndingGetting TogetherMutual PiningEmotional SexGentle SexLove ConfessionsOverthinkingLogical Hermione GrangerAwkward Sexual SituationsCrying During SexHermione Granger's POVPorn with FeelingsHarmony - FreeformHarry Potter - FreeformHogwarts Eighth YearChristmaswinter holidaysIntercrural Sexroom of requirement sexMissionary PositionBlanket cuddlesHumorTeasingDomestic Fluffbed sharingVoyeurismAwkwardnessCuddling & SnugglingSleeping TogetherKissingLoss of VirginityEmbarrassmentDobby (Harry Potter) - FreeforminterruptionsProtective Harry Potter\nSummary\nHarry has always been the hero, the chosen one, but he's never felt more powerless than when Hermione looks at him with fire in her eyes. When she takes control of their shared destiny, he realizes that being led by her is the greatest adventure of all.\nASSISTANT: Yeah, I see the problem immediately.\n\n**Title-summary mismatch is killing you.** \"The Headmaster's Gardening Tips\" sounds like a Dumbledore-centric humor fic, maybe crack, maybe something dark involving the greenhouses. The summary is a straightforward Harmony romance. These are marketing to two completely different audiences. People who click for the title aren't getting what they expected, and people searching for Harmony romance are scrolling right past because the title doesn't signal them.\n\n**\"Creator Chose Not To Use Archive Warnings\"** \u2014 This is a flag for many readers. Combined with a title that evokes Dumbledore and potential creepiness, some readers might assume the worst and nope out. Your other fic used \"No Archive Warnings Apply\" and was clearer about content.\n\n**The summary itself** \u2014 It's vague. \"Fire in her eyes,\" \"shared destiny,\" \"greatest adventure\" could describe 90% of Harmony fic. There's nothing specific to *this* story. What actually happens? What's the hook? The gardening title element isn't explained.\n\n**Tag sprawl** \u2014 50+ tags covering every possible micro-element from \"blanket cuddles\" to \"intercrural sex\" to \"Dobby.\" It's overwhelming and makes the tone hard to read. Is this fluff? Angst? Comedy? All of them? When everything is tagged, nothing is prioritized.\n\nThe high bookmark rate confirms the *writing* works. The discovery pipeline is what's broken.", "embedding": [-0.047903068363666534, -0.03475416079163551, 0.004648387897759676, 0.042118605226278305, -0.04669561609625816, 0.04716339334845543, 0.028387144207954407, 0.03442409634590149, -0.01775360479950905, -0.047810912132263184, -0.012989843264222145, -0.04040927067399025, -0.044256456196308136, 0.025403717532753944, 0.028485126793384552, -0.021429840475320816, 0.05898547172546387, -0.0024107573553919792, -0.07494678348302841, 0.03993866592645645, 0.055073082447052, -0.036859072744846344, 0.0607958622276783, -0.0578174851834774, -0.030787089839577675, -0.07056012749671936, -0.02126171626150608, 0.0013164605479687452, -0.04984210431575775, -0.05754667520523071, -0.032651498913764954, 0.004589678719639778, 0.011912363581359386, -0.030407028272747993, -0.041480641812086105, 0.002189114922657609, -0.011474735103547573, 0.11657418310642242, 0.07303416728973389, -0.07140863686800003, -0.046792156994342804, -0.09867161512374878, -0.07602349668741226, 0.0763772651553154, -0.0343874916434288, -0.027109811082482338, -0.03385185822844505, -0.0641605481505394, -0.06781666725873947, 0.009987353347241879, -0.024437271058559418, 0.03334253281354904, -0.003148142946884036, 0.02651965245604515, 0.04705675691366196, -0.053